      <section class="section-block-markdown-cell">
      <h3 id="Usage of Ollama Models">Usage of Ollama Models<a class="anchor-link" href="#Usage of Ollama Models"><img decoding="async" class="link-img" width="24px" height="24px" alt="link image 37" src={svg_paths.link_svg_path}/></a></h3>
      </section>
      
      <section class="section-block-markdown-cell">
      <p>As we have already seen in the post on <a href="https://www.maximofn.com/ollama">Ollama</a>, it is a framework built on <code>llama.cpp</code> that allows us to use language models easily and also supports quantized models.</p>
      <p>So let's see how to use <code>Qwen2.5 7B</code> with Ollama in Langchain.</p>
      </section>
      
      <section class="section-block-markdown-cell">
      <p>Before anything else, we need to install the Llama module from Langchain</p>
      <div class='highlight'><pre><code class="language-bash">pip install -U langchain-ollama</code></pre></div>
      </section>
      
      <section class="section-block-markdown-cell">
      <h4 id="Download model">Download model<a class="anchor-link" href="#Download model"><img decoding="async" class="link-img" width="24px" height="24px" alt="link image 38" src={svg_paths.link_svg_path}/></a></h4>
      </section>
      
